data.name: GeneralPhrases_RestDesription
data.value: Representational state transfer (REST) is a software architectural style which uses a subset of HTTP and is commonly used to create interactive applications that use Web services.

data.name: GeneralPhrases_RestSwaggerDesription
data.value: Swagger is an Interface Description Language for describing RESTful APIs expressed using JSON. Swagger is used together with a set of open-source software tools to design, build, document, and use RESTful web services. Swagger includes automated documentation, code generation (into many programming languages), and test-case generation.

data.name: GeneralPhrases_GraphQlDesription
data.value: GraphQL, developed internally by Facebook in 2012 and publicly released in 2015, is an open-source data query and manipulation language for APIs, and a runtime for fulfilling queries with existing data.

data.name: GeneralPhrases_GraphQlAltairDesription
data.value: Altair GraphQL is a client that assists in the debuging of GraphQL queries and implementations.

data.name: GeneralPhrases_GraphQlGraphiqlDesription
data.value: GraphiQL, the reference implementation, is an official GraphQL Foundation project

data.name: GeneralPhrases_GraphQlPlaygroundDesription
data.value: GraphQl Playground is and open-source GraphQL IDE for better development workflows.

data.name: GeneralPhrases_GraphQlVoyagerDesription
data.value: Voyager is a GraphqQL tool allowing the exploration of a GraphQL API as an interactive graph.
